t: Psalm 136
O*p give thanks unto the Lord;*s for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
O*p give thanks unto the God of gods: for his mercy endureth for ever.
O*p give thanks to the Lord of lords: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him who alone doeth great wonders: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him that by wisdom made the heavens: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him that stretched out the earth above the waters: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him that made great lights: for his mercy endureth for ever:
The*p sun to rule by day: for his mercy endureth for ever:
The*p moon and stars to rule by night: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him that smote Egypt in their firstborn: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy endureth for ever:
With*p a strong hand, and with a stretched out arm: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him which divided the Red sea into parts: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p made Israel to pass through the midst of it: for his mercy endureth for ever:
But*p overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red sea: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him which led his people through the wilderness: for his mercy endureth for ever.
To*p him which smote great kings: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p slew famous kings: for his mercy endureth for ever:
Sihon*p king of the Amorites: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p Og the king of Bashan: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p gave their land for an heritage: for his mercy endureth for ever:
Even*p an heritage unto Israel his servant: for his mercy endureth for ever.
Who*p remembered us in our low estate: for his mercy endureth for ever:
And*p hath redeemed us from our enemies: for his mercy endureth for ever.
Who*p giveth food to all flesh: for his mercy endureth for ever.
O*p give thanks unto the God of heaven: for his mercy endureth for ever.
